    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_197267">I don't even play and I think I understood it.<br />
<br />
Lets say, for instance, that A is scout skills and B is fighter skills and C is mage skills.<br />
<br />
So any player starts the wheel, now a series comes up with specific skills.  Like say,<br />
<br />
ACCABAAACCBBABBCC<br />
<br />
Each letter represents a specific skill, owned by a specific combo.  Now, to keep the combo going, someone in the group has to USE the correct skill to go on to the next skill.<br />
<br />
But sometimes you might not have, say, a mage.  So what do you do when you hit those Cs?  The combo would just stop there.<br />
<br />
But if you have a Scout, the scout has an ability that lets the combo skip that letter, moving to the next one that is hopefully possessed by someone in the group.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
