    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_197328">I thinks you got it DarthEnder! I haven't played much in a group, but that does sound more logical after I've had the opportunity to play with the Heroic Opportunities. Solo HOs are pretty easy and gets the job done fast. I can do small (2-3 light blues) grouped mobs amd win 99% of the time.<br />
<br />
At level 6, the solo Heroic Opportunity runs:<br />
<br />
Lucky Strike  Evade <i><b>OR</b></i> Cheap Shot  Quick Strike<br />
<br />
While I haven't really paid much attention to the end Heroic Opportunity frequency, I am guessing that in the situations where you have an option between 2 or more Combat Abilities, you are changing the end result. Nothing to prove this yet, but in my gut I think we'll be able to sway the end result based on the chain order.<br />
<br />
Currently (at level 6) there are 3 possible Heroic Opportunities. They seem random when they pop... all are nice little solo benefits.  <img src="images/smilies/emote_evil.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Evil" class="inlineimg" /> <br />
<ul><li><b>Bravo's Dance:</b> Attack speed buff<br />
<b>Ringing Blow:</b> Bringeth the smacketh down- DD crit.<br />
<b>Swindler's Luck:</b> Increases hit percentage.</li>
</ul>I assume this list will grow as you level and also require more complicated Combat Ability chains. In effect, we'll probably develop a chain handbook to selectively buff/direct damage on a whim.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
