    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_197791">the scout can't skip a stage and the scout can't choose an outcome.  What the scout can do (and only about half the time at that) is reject a wheel in the hopes of getting a different one.<br />
<br />
If the wheel that is up has a green coin off to the side (about 5'oclock position) then the scout can force the random a second time to possibly get a different wheel.  The second random is exactly like the first, so if you have the common wheel and force a redo you'll most likely get the common wheel again.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
