    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_197800">Still, the chance to reroll the wheel is pretty signifigant IMO.  I haven't been keeping up with this thread but the accurate information is in essence here.  The scout is the only class who can modify the result of the Heroic opportunity chain.  <br />
<br />
Basically they get to 'reroll' it to see if they get a more desired effect.  For example, the party is doing well but there is a lot of mobs; the rogue sees the end result of the chain (HO) will be a buff of some sort; the scout can reroll the efffect if he pulls of a move before the fist step of the HO is completed.  The scout/party has a chance of getting other 'heroic actions' from the list for that particular chain.  If memory serves there were two common results and one rare per chain.  <br />
<br />
Thus, instead of a buff that lasts for x minutes the party may end up getting a group heal or an AE damage effect (depends on the HO chain as to what is done -- and don't ask me how many there are, I don't know; most people didn't want to mess around with them enough when I was in beta and my playtime was limited).  I hope that clarifies for you guys!</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
