    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_198607">Well, you are all semi-correct. Right now scouts are the only ones who can influance the HO outside of activating, advancing, and completing them.<br />
<br />
Every other class can do the same things you can do, however. A scout can use their coin abilities, the ones used to activate HO. Examples are Dirty Tricks, Evade, Cheap Shot, Etc. Doing this will shift the HO if it isn't an effect you like. Example being, lets say you're soloing and it comes after you activate HO that it's Swindlers Luck (+10 combat skills for a few min) while you would much better benefit from Ringing Blow, if you used another coin skill. Lets use for this example, evade. Then it will throw up the HO again in another state, most of the time it changes between Swindlers Luck and Ringing Blow, sometimes it just repeats the last one and there is no change, sometimes you get a Bravo's Dance out of it. It's all pretty moronic for my tastes. The only place I feel that scouts do come in handy in that aspect is when in a full group, you can shift the group HO's to the highest damaging ones more often which does help.<br />
<br />
Just like they made it up to be from the start. At the start I read that Scouts would be the only ones to be able to start HO's so their presence in a group would make a really big difference. But as it is now, most of the better HOs dont even involve scout (mostly mage, cleric, fighter combos) However like I said being able to shift it to the high damage AoE stun attack is worth it if you can get it off more often.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
