    <div align="left" id="post_message_199342"><div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="middle">
	
	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>DarthEnder said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Lets say, for instance, that A is scout skills and B is fighter skills and C is mage skills.<br />
<br />
So any player starts the wheel, now a series comes up with specific skills.  Like say,<br />
<br />
ACCABAAACCBBABBCC<br />
<br />
Each letter represents a specific skill, owned by a specific combo.  Now, to keep the combo going, someone in the group has to USE the correct skill to go on to the next skill.<br />
<br />
But sometimes you might not have, say, a mage.  So what do you do when you hit those Cs?  The combo would just stop there.</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>From what I've read and seen of the group HOs so far, the starter chain that activates the HO is basically your opportunity to indicate what archetypes you have in your group. Once this is entered, then an HO comes up with icons for those archetypes. I don't think you can get an HO to come up requiring a mage if a mage is not there to hit their starter icon. Obviously the best HOs will be where each archetype hits their starter icon, resulting in a somewhat massive HO chain.<br />
<br />
In fact there probably is really no distinction mechanics wise between a solo or a group HO, it is only a matter of some other archetype being able to enter their starter icon.</div>
